This paper discusses the performance of different algorithms for K-medoids clustering, which is a subfield of machine learning and data mining. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DM (Data Mining) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of clustering in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV), which suggests that it could also be relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
